Comfycreations here, with a seventh chapter of qt kangaroo goodness for you guys. I can't say it enough, but I'm really sorry it took me this long to get the update done, but I hope after all the delays that the length and content makes up for it.
I appreciate the patience from all those who have read the story and have continued to look forward to it despite everything.

The 49.5k word update for A Roo'd Awakening can be found here: https://rentry.co/RoodChapterSeven/

The full story from the start can be found here: https://www.4binz.org/416 or here: https://rentry.co/RoodChapterOne but I'd suggest starting with the first link as the greentext bits read better there, and it contains a link to the prose chapters at the end.

Album with all story related art can be found here: https://catbox.moe/c/agt3hn

As always, I appreciate any and all feedback/criticism of any kind and length, whether positive or negative as it's helped me identify and stamp out issues with my writing. I really hope you guys enjoy the update, and to any people who might be reading for the first time I just want to say to not judge the start too harshly as it was written when I was very new to creative writing. And if you're turned off by the greentext aspect of that beginning, it's a very minor 25k or so words before the story goes into full prose writing. I intend to adjust that formatting to prose moving forward without doing any sort of rewriting beyond some slight polishing.

Lastly, I'd like to thank a few very important people for helping me make this update possible. I'd like to thank Tious for his help throughout every step of the way with feedback, ideas, proofreading/beta reading and way more stuff that I can't even put into words properly. Secondly, I'd like to also thank idontwantthis for helping with story direction, ideas, assisting in proofreading as well as providing feedback. I'd also like to thank Meklab for his help with extensive beta reading and feedback.
